Method behavioural requirements:
- The integer 2D array parameter `customers` must not be null.
- The integer 2D array parameter `customers` must have a length between 1 and 10^5.
- Each sub-array within the integer 2D array parameter `customers` must have a length of 2.
- The integer elements within each sub-array of the integer 2D array parameter `customers` must be between 1 and 10^4.
- The arrival times within the integer 2D array parameter `customers` must be sorted in non-decreasing order.
- The average waiting time of all customers must be returned as a double.